-- Crennel Named Coach of NFL’s Chiefs After Replacing Haley on Interim Basis
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-01-09T16:41:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/crennel-named-coach-of-nfl-s-chiefs-after-replacing-haley-on-interim-basis.html
Romeo Crennel was named coach of the
 Kansas City Chiefs  by general manager Scott Pioli.  “Romeo’s extensive knowledge of our players, personnel,
and needs make him a perfect fit to lead the Kansas City
Chiefs,” Pioli said in a statement.  Crennel, who was the defensive coordinator until being
appointed coach when Todd Haley was fired, compiled a 2-1
record. The Chiefs finished the season 7-9.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  